	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nintendulator and Nestopia are probably the most accurate on Windows. FCEUX is less accurate but available on lots of other platforms such as Linux. (I tried compiling Nestopia with the Linux patch some time ago, and all it did was freeze.)
<br />
<br />The best emulator for your needs probably depends on what you want to do with an accurate emulator. Are you trying to develop NES software without access to a PowerPak or other rewritable cartridge?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


